    "name": "ConvE",
    "description": "ConvE is introduced as a multi-layer convolutional network model designed for link prediction (predicting missing relationships between entities). The model reports state-of-the-art results on several established datasets and is highly parameter efficient, achieving performance comparable to DistMult and R-GCN while using 8x and 17x fewer parameters, respectively. Analysis suggests ConvE is particularly effective at modelling nodes with high indegree, which are common in complex knowledge graphs such as Freebase and YAGO3. After adapting the evaluation to robust dataset variants to counter test set leakage issues, ConvE achieved state-of-the-art Mean Reciprocal Rank across most datasets tested.",
